Philanthropy, Volunteerism & Grantmaking

The Center on Philanthropy and Public Policy


Learn More












The Leonetti O'Connell Family Foundation is dedicated to supporting grantees that serve Los Angeles County and its residents. Grants are only made to organizations that are tax-exempt under §501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code, and federal and state entities described in §170(c) of the Internal Revenue Code. The Foundation awards single year grants only. 








515 South Figueroa Street - Suite 1050 - Los Angeles, CA 90071
© Leonetti O'Connell Family Foundation 

















Leonetti / O’Connell Family Foundation















   



Menu





 
 



Grantees








The Leonetti/O'Connell Family Foundation does not accept unsolicited proposals. Grants are awarded based upon the interests and priorities of the foundation built upon grant commitments in designated strategic areas. Significant weight is given to programs that serve the Los Angeles County area.

Current Grantee Login
We accept grant applications by invitation only. The following instructions provide information for existing grantees and organizations we have invited to apply for support:


